 birds (2001) Condor, , in press; Peterson, A.T., Cohoon, K.P., Sensitivity of distributional prediction algorithms to geographic data completeness (1999) Ecol. Mod., 117, pp. 159-164; Peterson, A.T., Stockwell, D.R.B., Distributional prediction based on ecological niche modeling of primary occurrence data (2001) Predicting Species Distributions, , Scott, J.M. (Ed.). Island Press, Washington, DC (in press); Peterson, A.T., Vieglais, D.A., Predicting species invasions using ecological niche modeling (2001) BioScience, , in press; Peterson, A.T., Navarro-Sigüenza, A.G., Benítez-Díaz, H., The need for continued scientific collecting: A geographic analysis of Mexican bird specimens (1998) Ibis, 140, pp. 288-294; Peterson, A.T., Soberón, J., Sánchez-Cordero, V., Conservatism of ecological niches in evolutionary time (1999) Science, 285, pp. 1265-1267; Peterson, A.T., Ball, L.G., Cohoon, K.C., Predicting distributions of tropical birds (2001) Ibis, , in press; Peterson, A.T., Sánchez-Cordero, V., Soberón, J., Buddemeier, R.W., Bartley, J., Stockwell, D.R.B., Predicting biogeographic shifts based on ecological niche modeling of primary species occurrence data (2001) Climate Change, , submitted; Sala, O.E., Chapin III, F.S., Armesto, J.J., Berlow, E., Bloomfield, J., Dirzo, R., Huber-Sanwald, E., Wall, D.H., Global biodiversity scenarios for the year 2100 (2000) Science, 287, pp. 1770-1774; Stockwell, D.R.B., Noble, I.R., Induction of sets of rules from animal distribution data: A robust and informative method of data analysis (1992) Math Comp. Simul., 33, pp. 385-390; Stockwell, D.R.B., Peters, D., The GARP modeling system: Problems and solutions to automated spatial prediction (1999) Int. J. Geogr. Inf. Sci., 13, pp. 143-158; Stockwell, D.R.B., Peterson, A.T., Detecting bias in species distributional predictions (2001) Predicting Species Distributions, , Scott, J.M. (Ed.) Island Press, Washington, DC (in press); Tobler, W., Smooth pycnophylactic interpolation for geograph